  "issue_number": 1154,
  "issue_title": "Replace custom validators with Click primitives",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nCurrently there are a lot of custom validators across the codebase, which can be implemented using Click's built-in primitives (like using `IntRange` for `validate_issue_id`).\n\nExamples of such validators are: `validate_issue_id`, `require_valid_issue_id`, `require_valid_ss58` etc etc etc. \n\n## Motivation\n\nBesides the cleanup itself, at least the following problems are also addressed by moving to Click's validators:\n\n1. Validation is delayed past parse time. For example, `gitt admin set-owner BAD_ADDR` first calls `_resolve_contract_and_network(...)` (config load, RPC pick, possibly a contract address lookup) and only then runs `require_valid_ss58`. A typo in the SS58 string fails *after* doing infrastructure work that didn't need to happen. Same for `--bounty` and `--issue`. Moving validation onto the Click decorator rejects at parse time, before any side effect.\n\n2. `--help` does not document accepted values. `--network` claims \"(local, test, finney)\" in prose but `type=str` accepts anything; `--id` says \"integer\" but accepts 0, negatives, and `2**63 - 1`; Migrating everything to the `Choice` / `IntRange` / etc will make `--help` the authoritative reference automatically.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-13T01:29:52Z",
